title: Flight Simulator 2020 - POI's - Malta - Saint Agatha's Tower
description:
In this video we will fly over the Saint Agatha's Tower also known as the Red Tower. Saint Agatha's Tower (Maltese: Torri ta' Sant'Agata), also known as the Red Tower (Maltese: Torri l-AÄ§mar), MellieÄ§a Tower (Maltese: Torri tal-MellieÄ§a) or Fort Saint Agatha (Maltese: Forti Sant'Agata), is a large bastioned watchtower in MellieÄ§a, Malta. It was built between 1647 and 1649, as the sixth of the Lascaris towers. The tower's design is completely different from the rest of the Lascaris towers, but it is similar to the earlier Wignacourt towers. St. Agatha's Tower was the last large bastioned tower to be built in Malta.
